  <front>
   <head>SONNET [13] XIII. From Petrarch.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="tetrameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">OH! place me where the burning noon</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Forbids the wither'd flow'r to blow;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Or place me in the frigid zone,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">On mountains of eternal snow:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Let me pursue the steps of Fame,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Or Poverty's more tranquil road;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Let youth's warm tide my veins inflame,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Or sixty winters chill my blood:</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Tho' my fond soul to Heav'n were flown,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Or tho' on Earth 'tis doom'd to pine,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Prisoner or free — obscure or known,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">My heart, oh Laura! still is thine.</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whate'er my destiny may be,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That faithful heart, still burns for thee!</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
